dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4413. Alternate title: Zara, Yugoslavia-Italy. Universal transverse Mercator and North Italy zone grids. UTM grid added, gradient tints and isogonic data deleted by AMS, 1947. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and and spot elevations. With a Serb and Croat glossary. Intelligence reports up to Nov. 1943. Compiled and drawn by War Office, 1944. Geographic area is designated as Yugoslavia/Italy it is now Croatia. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1947.
dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Zara, sheet Y-22. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4413).
